summary: LETTERR ON BEHALF OF ORLAND BREUNIG (WI). MR. BREUNIG  WAS OPPOSED TO EARLY WARNING REPORTING (EWR) REGULATION WHICH REQUIRED 500 MANUFACTURERS OF SMAL TO MEDIUM TRAILERS (THOSE  WITH A GROSS VEHICLE WEIGHT RATING, GVWR, OF UNDER 16000 POUNDS) TO SUBMIT COMPREHENSIVE EARLY WARNING REPORTS TO NHTS. MR BREUNIG INDICATED  THAT EWR WOULD BE UNFAIR TO MANUFACTURER'S. IT WOULD CREATE A FINANCIAL BURDEN, AND COULD PUT HIM AND SOME OF HIS COLLEAGUES OUT OF BUSINESS.  *JB....*AK
